you're wrong.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: What's your next line of questioning?

choices.string: What have you been doing today?
Can you tell me about anyone else?
Listen, I report to people higher than you do, so lets cut to the chase OK?
Did you know that by helping the right person you could get a raise very quickly here?
What can you tell me about yourself?

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I believe I was patrolling the Caf. Not necessarily my favorite part of the job.
Im sorry, I dont know anyone by that name.
I was at the gym, Im there daily.
I was doing paperwork in the office. We do a lot of that too, just so you know.
There was a case of Vibro-Shurikens smuggled out of security recently. Josh is our prime suspect, be careful around him.
Ive seen that kid holding a metal pipe down in the Belly, looking like hes in some mob film.
People in the Belly somehow get their hands on eSwords every now and then and Josh is definitely one of them. Im confident hes not using it for good reasons.
Declaring trust variables based off detective archetype.
Displaying a greeting based off of the trust variable. 1 is the max value
Detective, dont you have actual criminals to go bother?
Detective.
How can I help you, Detective?
ALIBI SECTION
This is the section where they confirm what weapons they caught other people using.
Guys got a laser on him. Its legal for people to have them but its rare enough for it to cause suspicion. Make sure you dont scare him.
Reports say hes selling radioactive ice cubes. Thats why I dont drink anything with water in it.
Im not sure if your rank is one Im supposed to answer to.
What chase?
Maybe I should find them then.
I work security for the worlds biggest security company. Cant say I always dreamed of being a top tier Mall Cop but the job is fulfilling.
How'd you find that? Must have got it from Mrs. Shi, huh? What a nice women.
[You don't have anything of interest.]
That little! Sorry maam! That perps been on my watchlist for what seems like ages now.
What do you want?
Hi.
Oh hey, what's up?

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: What kind of questioning are we dealing with now?

choices.string: What can you tell me about other people?
Arent you a little young to be out here by yourself? Itd be sooo easy for me to contact your supervisor...
Ive read your reports from YAP, theyre impressive.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I was at the gym, doing what do you think?
I tried that new extreme caffeine mocha-late grande duplex viente at the Caf.
As you might know if youve done your job, Im a member of the YAP. I was at the office filling in some boring papers, as always.
Depends on who.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Depends on who.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Im sorry I wasnt paying attention. Go ask someone else.
You know the security detail got a package of V.S.s lately. What will they use that for, even?
Ive seen Liam hide a metal pipe away once. Either that was a lost and found item or he has something sketchy going on. Whatever, doesnt matter to me.
Ive seen him hold an eSword every now and then. Its disturbing watching a security guard play with his sword while hes on duty.
He may be a guard but I saw him once with a laser pistol and like those things are scary. Theyre silent and kill people instantly.
I once saw him stash a package of radioactive ice cubes in his pockets. I dont know where he got them from but I wouldnt drink anything around him.
Liam is a security guard for the escalator to the Belly. I kinda keep notes on his schedule so I can sneak down there. You seem cool so dont tell anyone.
Do you honestly think anyone cares?
It was nothing, dont worry about it.
Well I joined YAP six months ago, when my GAC scores came home. You know, I get it, its a great opportunity but Its so much work, you know? I just wanna have fun!
Personal Object ->
O M G, where did you find that?! Please, dont tell Noel!
[You don't have a personal object to show her]
I know a lot of Joshs, nothing about their last names, and nothing about them.
Hey.
Yo, wassup D.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: What's your next line of questioning?

choices.string: Can you tell me about someone else?
I believe art is not everything you deal with, right?
I hear youre an artists of sorts...

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I was at the gym, working on my sales muscles.
I was at the caf, writing my novel. Love, hate, betrayal Its gonna be amazing.
Yeah, I was at the office. Ive got a job too, you know? A legit one and stuff. Everyone has one, so what?
Liam OShea? That sounds like a fake name.
Shes bought some V.S.s off me awhile ago. Dont know what theyre for but its a strange order; those things are rare.
I once saw her leave the alleyway with a metal pipe in hand. She told me it was for protection but the way she held it showed experience.
Did you know she has an eSword? She told me she usually keeps it in her room but she once brought it here because she said he needed the protection. It was creepy how well she held it.
She recently bought a laser pistol off me. Those things come at a high price, I dont know what use she has it though so I wont ask.
Be careful around her though, shes been known to hold radioactive ice cubes with her.
I dont owe you anything, miss detective.
Some people call everything I offer artistic in some way.
Are you trying to make fun of me?
Im a life-lover, art-breather and respectful citizen who tries to bring some color to this gray world of oppression. I free minds and bodies throughout the ship, and people respect me for that, dude.
Oh yeah, this Carlos guy gave me this in exchange for a new one that allows access to the Fin. Guys pretty cool, but he should take better care of this equipment, its worth a lot you know?
[You don't have a personal object to show him]
Youd be amazed if you knew the amount of girls I get to know by my job. Nina happens to be one of them, so what?
Why are you wasting my time?
Im a busy man, what do you want?
What can I do for you? Please, make it quick.

choices.string: What can you tell me about other people?
Stop pretending, I can tell you dont have anything for me.
Thank you for the help, your skills are crucial for this case.
So why are you on the ship?

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Liam what? Oh, wait. Yeah. Hes one of the security guys, right? Ive seen him a couple times but I dont really know him.
I don't know what I can tell you about her.
She tends to buy things from this dealer named whatshisface. I think I saw some V.S.s, or Vibro-Shuriken, on her person recently. Hopefully she didnt have use of them but Ill let her live her life.
She goes to shady places often, but she can take care of herself. I see her carrying a metal pipe sometimes, its way too big for her size but she has a good grip on it.
She has her own eSword that she usually keeps at home. The only times Ive seen her bring it outside was during show and tell years ago and again recently when she went to the Belly.
I know she a laser pistol recently, but Im only assuming she has the proper paperwork for it.
Shes been known to carry radioactive ice cubes on her but I like to think that its precautionary.
Keep saying that and fail at your job. Does it look like I care?
I know. And I also know what youre trying to do and its not going to happen.
Im not really allowed to talk about anything that isnt public, you know. Anything you need to know about me youll find in my public profile.
[You don't have a personal object to present to him]
Oh yeah, sometimes the kids think they escaped but I just let them roam around. Its cute.
Ive never heard that name, next question.
Ah, Nina. I love that brat. She works for me. What has she done this time?
Good day to you, Detective.
Good day to you, Jane.
Hello sweetie, its nice seeing you again.

choices.string: What can you tell me about other people?
You must be very smart for making your business so successful in this area...
I really wanted to talk to you, youre well respected here. Thanks for the help.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Liam is a nice kid, he still frequents this place.
Its so strange that hes a guard now. I still see him as a kid, so I actually scolded him recently when I saw him carrying V.S.s.
He brought a metal pipe here recently, said it was confiscated.
I kicked him out recently when he brought an eSword with him to the shop. Those things are too dangerous to be handled in public.
I still see him as a kid, so its strange seeing him wield a laser pistol.
I love the boy but he brought confiscated radioactive ice cubes to my stall recently. Does he know I can lose a ton of business just by having those seen near here?
I take that as a compliment, young lady.
Issit? Ive always said that if you treat people with respect and care for them thats what you get back. The snobs from upstairs could learn a thing or two from those in the Belly, lah.
Its been so long since I got here, and days go by so fast when youre of a certain age Thanks for asking, but Im sure that knowing the life of an old shopkeeper wont really help your case.
Oh, this is my son with Liam. They were so young back then, good friends too!
[You don't have anything to present to her.]
Im sorry detective, I get to see so many people throughout the day My memory isnt as good as it used to be.
Josh is...umm, Im sorry I dont know anyone by that name.
I think Nina visits my shop with her friends every now and then, but I dont know anything about her Im sorry.
Huh? Wha?
Yo.
Amiga!
What do you want.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: What's your next question?

choices.string: Can you tell me about anyone else?
You seem like someone that someone else is looking for...
Do you want to go for a drink later? If I get to solve this case, that is...
We can pick this up later.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Who do you wanna know about?

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I dont know many people from the Fin, sorry.
Guy was holding a lot of stuff. The coolest thing was a box of V.Ss.
Guy usually deals in an alley-way so its not too uncommon to see him with a metal pipe in hand.
Hes told me that he doesnt own an eSword but I saw him carrying one once in passing.
I wouldnt try to rob the guy, he carries a laser pistol on him.
One of the cheapest things he sells is radioactive ice cubes. Why are those cheap? I cant drink without a second look anymore...
I hope that someone is you, guapa.
Oh, s mami!
Grew up in the Belly, gained some character. Got a pass to the Fin, gained some money. Thats my life in a nutshell.
Isnt it amazing that they make such perfect replicas of these things? I think that guy Josh is an artist when it comes to these.
[You don't have anything to show him.]
Are we cool? Idunno yet.
Nah, is she hot?
Uuummmmm. no (wink). Never bought anything from him, promise! Especially not unregistered passes to the Fin. But he sounds cool.
